    pmh: ["Contact lens wearer", "Diabetes"],
    barriers: [],
    recent_notes: "47yo diabetic male contact lens wearer with red, painful left eye x2 days. Decreased vision. Photophobia. Wears contacts overnight sometimes. Exam: Left eye conjunctival injection, cornea appears hazy, hypopyon noted. Assessment: Conjunctivitis. Artificial tears and follow-up.",
    labs: "No fluorescein exam. CRITICAL: Contact lens wearer + painful red eye + decreased vision + HYPOPYON (pus in anterior chamber) = BACTERIAL KERATITIS or ENDOPHTHALMITIS. This is an ocular emergency. Pseudomonas keratitis in contact lens wearers can perforate cornea within 24 hours. Hypopyon indicates severe infection. Need STAT ophthalmology consult, corneal cultures, fortified antibiotic drops (fluoroquinolone or tobramycin/cefazolin). This is NOT conjunctivitis - conjunctivitis is painless without vision changes."
