    pmh: ["Heavy menstrual periods"],
    barriers: [],
    recent_notes: "41yo female with fatigue x2 months. Has heavy periods. CBC shows Hgb 7.8, MCV 68 (microcytic). Stool guaiac negative in office. Assessment: Iron deficiency anemia from menorrhagia. Iron supplements and outpatient follow-up.",
    labs: "Hgb 7.8, MCV 68, ferritin not checked. CRITICAL: Severe microcytic anemia (Hgb 7.8) requires FULL WORKUP before assuming menorrhagia is cause. Need iron studies (ferritin, TIBC, serum iron), reticulocyte count. If iron deficiency confirmed in patient over 40, needs GI workup to rule out COLON CANCER - cannot assume it's all from periods. Need colonoscopy and EGD. Stool guaiac can be negative with slow bleeding. Colon cancer can present with iron deficiency anemia."
